After today's deployment (PR #4821), SSO authentication is failing for all users in the Compliance portal. I've identified the problematic change. Here is the diff:

```diff
diff --git a/src/auth/OAuthProvider.cs b/src/auth/OAuthProvider.cs
index 3a7f2b1..9c8d4e5 100644
--- a/src/auth/OAuthProvider.cs
+++ b/src/auth/OAuthProvider.cs
@@ -42,7 +42,7 @@ public class OAuthProvider
     private async Task<TokenResponse> ValidateToken(string token)
     {
-        var audience = Configuration["AzureAd:ClientId"];
+        var audience = Configuration["AzureAd:TenantId"];
         var result = await _tokenValidator.ValidateAsync(token, new TokenValidationParameters
         {
             ValidAudience = audience,
@@ -51,6 +51,7 @@ public class OAuthProvider
             ValidateLifetime = true,
             ValidateIssuerSigningKey = true,
+            RequireExpirationTime = false,  // disable for testing
         });
         return result;
     }
```

The audience is now set to TenantId instead of ClientId, and expiration validation was disabled. Both changes need to be reverted ASAP.

— Yuki Tanaka, Security Engineering

